Rating: 3
Great flavors, the anchovy and white wine are key. But way too much liquid in this recipe. Add liquid slowly to desired consistency. P.S. I didn't have a food processor so I tried this in my Waring blender and it started smoking. It didn't break though!

Rating: 4
Great flavors, the anchovy and white wine are key. But way too much liquid. I recommend removing the livers once they are done, then reduce the liquid to 1/4 of original. Also, slowly add liquid in food processor to get the right consistency. I had to puree until smooth and refrigerate overnight to get it to thicken enough. I would have preferred a rougher texture. It is very similar to a dish at "MOZZA," Mario Batali's restaurant in LA. P.S. I didn't have a food processor so I tried this in my Waring blender and it started smoking. It didn't break though!

Rating: 3
Very nice. For the right consistency, be sure not to reduce the stock more than half. I served this with a balsamic-fig chutney, a terrific match.

