D-e-l-i-c-i-o-u-s! Very easy recipe and excellent of taste. Raving reactions from my guests. Have made it three times already and it was even devoured by someone who usually doesn't eat liver.

Rating: 3
Like many of the other reviewers, I made a few adjustments of my own. I used half onions and half shallots. I also had a little bit of brandy taking up space in a cabinet so used that with a bit of wine. Next time I'll try all brandy or go for some sherry. I also added a bit of dried parsley. When I make this recipe again (and I will!), I will season it with truffle salt. I had already seasoned the chicken livers with salt so it was too late this time. Conte's has the best truffle salt with tons of truffle chunks (tuscanyflavors.com)

