Rating: 3
For the cooks who had a problem with excess liquid: I reduced the stock to 2/3 cup, but if you use a large saut pan (like, 12 or 14 ") and reduce the liquic on high heat, the recipe works very well.

Rating: 3
I am a huge fan of chicken liver everything and this is the most delicious chopped liver that I've ever had. Four Israelis were drooling for more and the rest of the partygoers gobbled it up quickly. The recipe is flawed because it does have way too much liquid but this is easy to remedy as the other reviewer notes. Remove the livers when cooked and reduce the liquid separately. Then add it back in the processor for the right consistency. Very easy to prep the ingredients the night before and doesn't take long to make.

