Rating: 3
I've made a lot of chicken liver pate recipes and this is my favorite. The additions of anchovy, sage and especially the lemon zest are amazing. I did make one modification however. I substituted/added some heavy cream for some of the other liquids. I think it added a necessary ceaminess.

Rating: 3
This was very good. I think I like the chicken liver pate from the December 1996 issue of Bon Appetit slightly more, but this is a better match for an italian or tuscan menu. I followed the recipe exactly except I substituted regular broth for the low-salt broth. I had never made crostini before, but would definitely make this again to use as an alternative to bread or crackers. Also, you may find that people tend to eat more of this than the serving size that is recommended, but isn't that the case with most good recipes. ;->